# WHAT IT IS
#   `jackpoint` solves the "what happens when Claude Code hits a
#   permission prompt and you're not at your laptop?" problem.  It
#   wraps the Anthropic `claude` CLI (or any other process) in a
#   tmux pane, injects Claude Code's `--settings` hook configuration
#   so that every Claude lifecycle event pings a local Unix-domain-
#   socket IPC server, and bridges those events bidirectionally to
#   a Matrix room of your choice via `matrix-js-sdk`.  From any
#   Matrix client (Element on phone, FluffyChat, Cinny web, the
#   Matrix iOS app, schildi.chat, the Hydrogen browser client) you
#   can:
#
#     • See live notifications when Claude starts a new session
#       (with the cwd / git-root / hostname / tmux pane context)
#     • See `AskUserQuestion` prompts mid-session and reply
#       directly from the Matrix room — the reply is keystroke-
#       injected into the Claude tmux pane via `tmux send-keys`
#     • See Claude's "I'm waiting for your input" idle prompts
#       (with the last assistant message extracted from the JSONL
#        transcript file)
#     • Approve / reject permission dialogs from the Matrix room
#       (Claude's `PreToolUse(AskUserQuestion)` /
#       `Notification(permission_prompt)` hook events)
#     • See the final tail of the assistant transcript when a
#       session ends (`Stop` event)
#
#   Because the bridge layer is purely Matrix-based, Element's
#   end-to-end encryption protects the entire pipeline by default
#   (the `@matrix-org/matrix-sdk-crypto-wasm` library handles
#   Olm + Megolm + device verification for the messages flowing
#   between your phone and the laptop running `jackpoint`).
#
#   The setup wizard (`jackpoint --setup`) walks you through
#   creating a Matrix account on `matrix.org` or any homeserver,
#   linking the wizard-generated device key, and pinning the
#   target room ID.  The configuration is stored in
#   `~/.config/jackpoint/config.json` and the Matrix session
#   credentials are stored in `~/.config/jackpoint/session.json`.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from claude-matrix.js +
#                       matrix-bridge.js + matrix-listener.js
#                       sources; extracted via
#                       raw.githubusercontent.com fetch)
#
#   jackpoint <PROGRAM> [PROGRAM-ARGS...]
#   jackpoint -s | --setup
#
#   The wrapper has minimal arg surface — the first positional arg
#   is the program to wrap (typically `claude` for Claude Code,
#   but any process with Claude-Code-style hooks works), and all
#   remaining args pass through unmodified.
#
#   Setup:
#     -s, --setup                    Run the interactive setup
#                                    wizard (Matrix login, device-
#                                    key generation, target-room
#                                    selection; writes
#                                    `~/.config/jackpoint/
#                                    config.json` +
#                                    `~/.config/jackpoint/
#                                    session.json`)
#
#   Wrap mode  (all other invocations):
#     <PROGRAM> [ARGS...]            Wrap PROGRAM in a tmux pane
#                                    and bridge its Claude-Code-
#                                    style hooks to Matrix
#                                    Examples:
#                                      jackpoint claude
#                                      jackpoint claude --model
#                                                       sonnet
#                                      jackpoint claude
#                                                 --resume
#                                                 <session-id>
#                                      jackpoint
#                                        opencode-cli ...
#                                      jackpoint goose ...
#
#   Environment:
#     MATRIX_DEBUG=1                 Enable verbose `[Jackpoint]` +
#                                    `[Hook]` + `[Matrix]` trace
#                                    output to stderr
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `artpi/jackpoint` declares **direct** dependencies on
#   `matrix-js-sdk@^40.0.0` AND `@matrix-org/matrix-sdk-crypto-wasm`
#   in its `package.json` (verified via `gh api repos/artpi/
#   jackpoint/contents/package.json`).  The source imports both
#   directly:
#
#     // matrix-bridge.js (the room/event abstraction layer):
#     import * as sdk from "matrix-js-sdk";
#     const client = sdk.createClient({
#       baseUrl, accessToken, userId, deviceId,
