#
#   `matrix-org/matrix-js-sdk` is **THE canonical TS/JS Matrix
#   protocol SDK** — the Element team's official reference
#   implementation of the Matrix Client-Server API, maintained
#   directly by the Matrix.org Foundation engineers
#   (Florian Duros, Hubert Chathi, Patrick Cloke, Michael Telatynski,
#   Robin Townsend, Travis Ralston, Andrew Morgan, plus the Element
#   web client team).  It is the **library that `element.io` itself
#   is built on** — every release of Element Web ships the latest
#   matrix-js-sdk as its core, and every browser-based Matrix
#   client either depends on matrix-js-sdk directly or on a
#   downstream fork (`@vector-im/matrix-bot-sdk`, `@groovehq/
#   matrix-bot-sdk`, `@nordeck/matrix-bot-sdk`, etc.).
#
#   The SDK exposes:
#
#     • The typed `MatrixClient` (constructed via
#       `sdk.createClient({baseUrl, accessToken, userId,
#       deviceId, cryptoStore})`) with full session management
#       (`client.startClient(opts)`, `client.stopClient()`,
#       `client.login(loginType, data)`, `client.loginRequest(
