#       `m.policy.rule.{user,room,server}`,
#       `m.room_key`, `m.room_key_request`,
#       `m.forwarded_room_key`, `m.secret.{request,send}`,
#       `m.secret_storage.{default_key,key.<keyId>}`,
#       `org.matrix.msc1772.{create,child,parent}` (Spaces
#       MSC), `org.matrix.msc3401.call`, `org.matrix.msc3489.beacon`,
#       `org.matrix.msc4143.rtc.member` (Element Call native
#       group calls) — every event kind exposed as a typed
#       `MatrixEvent` with full `event.getContent()`,
#       `event.getType()`, `event.getSender()`,
#       `event.getRoomId()`, `event.getId()`,
#       `event.getOriginalContent()` (the decrypted plaintext,
#       if the event was E2EE-wrapped), `event.isEncrypted()`,
#       `event.isDecryptionFailure()`,
#       `event.shouldAttemptDecryption()`,
#       `event.getStateKey()`, `event.getTs()`,
#       `event.getDate()`, `event.getThread()`,
#       `event.getRelation()` typed methods
#
#     • Typed `Room` and `RoomMember` and `RoomState` classes
#       with full membership / power-level / encrypted-channel
#       lifecycle, `room.timeline`, `room.getJoinedMembers()`,
#       `room.getReceiptsForEvent(event)`,
